Name: COMMODITIES
Conclusion: Geneva, 17 October 1955, and New York, 15 November 1955
EIF: The International Agreement on Olive Oil, 1956, which was drawn up at the first session of the United Nations Conference on Olive Oil held at Geneva from 3 to 17 October 1955 and opened for signature at the Headquarters of the United Nations did not come into force [see the Protocol amending the International Agreement on Olive Oil, 1956 (chapter XIX.2) and the International Agreement on Olive Oil, 1956, as amended by the Protocol of 3 April 1958 (chapter XIX.3)].
